The Uber Pass membership benefits in Australia include:

* At least 10% off every trip (excluding UberPool)

* $0 Delivery Fee for orders over $20 (before fees) from Grocery, Convenience, and Alcohol stores on Uber Eats (*Service Fee still applies*)

If a benefit didn’t apply to your trip/order, you can report the issue by answering the questions in the in-app form.

To change or cancel an order in AU, follow these steps:

1. If you never received your order but were charged, use the in-app link "Order Never Arrived".
2. If you had an issue with the delivery person, use the link "I Had an Issue With My Delivery Person".
3. If your order was wrong or incomplete, use the link "Wrong or Missing Items".
4. If you believe you were incorrectly charged or have questions about an authorization hold, see "I Think I Was Charged More Than Once".

If a merchant cancels your order before delivery begins, you will not be charged.

However, if you cancel after the delivery has begun, you may be charged the full price for any Uber Eats delivery services. For Non-Restaurant Food merchants, once delivery has begun, you will no longer be able to cancel your order without incurring a charge, which will be no more than the full price for your ordered items and the full price for any Uber Eats delivery services.

To change or cancel an order on Uber Eats in AU, follow these steps:

* For restaurant orders:
	+ If the merchant hasn't accepted your order yet, you can cancel at any time without incurring a charge.
	+ If the merchant has accepted your order and you cancel 2 minutes or more after placing it, you'll incur a cancellation charge (no more than the full price of your ordered items).
* For Non-Restaurant Food orders:
	+ You may cancel your order at any time.
	+ Once delivery has begun, you will no longer be able to cancel your order without incurring a charge, which will be no more than the full price for your ordered items and the full price for any Uber Eats delivery services.

To cancel an order, tap **Cancel Order** in the order tracking screen. If you have issues or concerns regarding your order, contact our support team.

To change or cancel an order from a restaurant on Uber Eats in AU, you can do so at any time before the merchant accepts your order without incurring a charge. If the merchant has already accepted your order and you cancel 2 minutes or more after placing it, you will incur a cancellation charge (no more than the full price of your ordered items).

If you purchase items from a non-restaurant food merchant, you may cancel your order at any time. However, once delivery has begun, you will no longer be able to cancel your order without incurring a charge, which will be no more than the full price for your ordered items and the full price for any Uber Eats delivery services [customer-order-cancellation-au-v1--0, customer-order-cancellation-au-v1--1].
